# AI Coding Assistant Rules

## General
- NEVER perform DOM rendering or browser-based testing/verification (using `browser_subagent` or similar tools) unless specifically asked by the user.
- Focus on code quality, architecture, and adherence to the project's "Clinical Emerald" and "Quiet Premium" design system.

## Design System
- Use "Clinical Emerald" colors (e.g., `bg-emerald-900`, `text-emerald-900`).
- Maintain "Quiet Premium" aesthetics (serif fonts for headings, clean vertical rhythm, professional spacing).
- Follow the guidelines in `EDITORIAL_GUIDE.md` for content and layout.

## Version Control
- NEVER perform git commands (add, commit, push) unless explicitly requested by the USER.
